                    <span>I've used this book as a constant reference over the last six years while  a facilitator for BPR and Change Management projects. Although it may lack  a comprehensive array of practical exercies and techniques for all  situations that arise in meetings or during facilitated focus group  sessions, it is by far the best reference. Once you read, re-read, and  fully understand the basics that Doyle and Straus are presenting, you can  modify and add your own experience and methods.</span>
                  
              
